context: <a0_0><b3_0>Lossless audio compression<b3_0/><a0_0/> produces a representation of digital data that decompress to an exact digital duplicate of the original audio stream, unlike playback from lossy compression techniques such as Vorbis and MP3. <a1_0><b4_0>Compression ratios<b4_0/><a1_0/> are around <b7_0>50–60% of original size<b7_0/>, which is similar to those for generic lossless data compression. <a2_0><b5_0>Lossless<b5_0/><a2_0/> compression is unable to attain high compression ratios due to the complexity of waveforms and the rapid changes in sound forms. Codecs like <b6_0>FLAC, Shorten and TTA<b6_0/> use linear prediction to estimate the spectrum of the signal.
